    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="492"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.113/10547a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Collector of Customs at Douglas, Arizona</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="67" xml:id="d492fn67">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                        mutandis</hi>, to the Collector of Customs at Nogales, Arizona, mentioning
                        Nogales, Mexico, as the place which surrendered.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-01">May 1,
                            1929</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mexican Embassy at Washington has advised this Department that Agua Prieta
                    surrendered to Federals this morning, that rebel troops are without necessary
                    food supplies, and requested that no further restrictions be placed on
                    exportation of food and other supplies. You are accordingly authorized to permit
                    unrestricted exportation of all food and other supplies not specifically covered
                    by embargo proclamation of January 7, 1924.<note n="68" xml:id="d492fn68">
                        <ref target="frus1924v02#pg_428">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1924, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 428</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry L. Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
